The inimitable @nojo18 is the cover star for our January magazine 💥

Wearing an @adidas X @gucci suit, the double world 200m champion tells @athletics.weekly why he wants to raise the profile of track and field for the next generation 💬

Through his docuseries “The Unseen Journey”, @nojo18 has showcased what it’s like to be an athlete behind the scenes - the emotions, dedication and sacrifice 🎬

On the track, he wants to target the world 200m record in 2023. Off it, he wants to advise the next generation that T&F is also a business and the importance of marketing yourself 🏟️

@nojo18 opens up about the mental, physical and emotional aspects that are part of breaking new barriers and why T&F is much more than just times 🧠

He also reveals how he was inspired by John Carlos and Tommie Smith at the 1968 Olympics 🇺🇸

“I’m not a shy man, I take every opportunity and if one doesn’t appear then I will find a way to create one,” @nojo18 says. 

Read the full interview via the @athletics.weekly website.

The best in the world are coming to Running City USA.

International track and field stars are returning to Atlanta this May in a way that hasn’t been seen since the 1996 Olympics. The inaugural adidas Atlanta City Games will be held in Centennial Olympic Park on May 6, 2023.

Noah Lyles, 3x World Champion, Olympic Bronze Medalist and current American record holder in the 200m, is one of the first to announce his intention to compete. Not only will there be professional athletes, but we will also host the inaugural adidas Running City Mile which is open to the public to participate in and waves will be separated by age group. Registration is limited and open now at the link in bio. 

Read more about the adidas Atlanta City Games and adidas Running City Mile at the #linkinbio
